data.title: A nice addition to the choices on the Square in Tyler .
data.text: I really like this place and is a five minute walk from my home on South College , Food is really good and the back room comfortable with a cool design ... I wish they were open more evenings !! Friendly staff and the food will bring me back often

data.title: Great Atmosphere
data.text: The food was pretty good, kind of pricey but nice place to hang out while you eat lunch. If you do go, try to stick with the Mexican food.

data.title: Excellent Breakfast Items
data.text:
Three of us ate there for breakfast and we enjoyed our meals tremendously. I had an omelet while the other two ordered the breakfast croissant that looked delicious and they loved it. I'll try that next time. They also had the fruit cup on the side which was fresh and juicy.  The place was not busy and it took a while to get our order but it was worth the wait since everything was so FRESH!

It's a family run business and the young boys you see waiting on tables and taking cash are the owners sons.
